text: Sisseton is a city in the northeastern part of the U.S. state of South Dakota. It is the county seat of Roberts County, and 2,479 people lived there at the 2020 census. Sisseton became a city in 1907. == References == == Other websites == *City of Sisseton website Category:County seats in South Dakota Category:Cities in South Dakota Category:1907 establishments in the United States Category:1900s establishments in South Dakota
